17)What are negative indexes and why are they used? 
Answer:-
Negative indexes in programming, most commonly used in Python, are a way to access elements in a sequence (such as lists, tuples, or strings) by counting backward from the end rather than the beginning. While normal indexing starts at \(0\) for the first element, negative indexing starts at-1 for the last element.

