28)Differentiate between append () and extend () methods? 
Answer:-
append(): Adds the whole list as one element, creating a nested structure.
list = [1, 2]
list.append([3, 4])
print(list)
Output:- Result: [1, 2, [3, 4]]
extend(): Unpacks the list and adds the numbers separately.
list = [1, 2]
list.extend([3, 4])
print(list)
Output:-[1, 2, 3, 4]

